.TH LORD 1 "June 2026" "exec" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
lord \- run Codex with a clear AGENTS profile
.SH SYNOPSIS
.SY lord
.RI [ option | @mode | @option ]...
.RI [ prompt ...]
.YS
.SY pray
.RI [ repo | unix | book | chat ]
.YS
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B lord
is a small wrapper around
.BR "codex exec" .
It chooses an AGENTS profile, applies a few Codex flags, runs the prompt
through Codex, and caches captured stdout.
.PP
There are four profiles:
.TP
.B @repo
Repository and code work.  This is the default inside a Git worktree.
.TP
.B @unix
Unix-filter work: read stdin, transform it, and print only the requested
output.  This is the default outside a Git worktree.
.TP
.B @book
Long-form explanation, exegesis, and careful reading.
.TP
.B @chat
Question-answering mode.  It answers the prompt directly and avoids touching
the current worktree.
.PP
If
.I ./AGENTS.md
is a real local file or an unrelated local symlink,
.B lord
leaves it alone.  If
.I ./AGENTS.md
is one of
.BR lord 's
own profile links,
.B lord
may replace it with the selected profile and removes the link when the run
finishes.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.BR -h ", " --help
Print help and exit.
.TP
.BR -v ", " --verbose
Print verbose wrapper behavior to stderr and run Codex without capturing
stdout.
.TP
.BR -f ", " --force
Pass
.B --dangerously-bypass-approvals-and-sandbox
through to
.BR "codex exec" .
.TP
.BR --effort " " LEVEL ", " --effort= LEVEL ", " @effort= LEVEL
Set Codex reasoning effort.
.I LEVEL
must be
.BR low ,
.BR medium ,
.BR high ,
or
.BR xhigh .
.TP
.BR --fast ", " @fast
Request low Codex reasoning effort.
.TP
.BR --careful ", " @careful
Request high Codex reasoning effort.
.TP
.BR --xhigh ", " @xhigh
Request extra-high Codex reasoning effort.
.TP
.BR --profile " " NAME ", " --profile= NAME ", " @profile= NAME
Select a profile by name.
.I NAME
must be
.BR repo ,
.BR unix ,
.BR book ,
or
.BR chat .
Legacy aliases
.BR git ,
.BR code ,
.BR command ,
.BR unix-command ,
.BR filter ,
.BR bible ,
.BR nameless ,
.BR we-the-nameless ,
.BR ask ,
.BR question ,
and
.B qa
are accepted.
.TP
.BR --no-agents ", " @no-agents
Do not install an AGENTS.md profile.
.TP
.B @echo
Print the
.B codex exec
command that would be run instead of running it.
.TP
.B @yhwh
Pass
.B --skip-git-repo-check
to Codex and do not use an AGENTS file.  This legacy option remains for the
.BR yhwh (1)
wrapper.
.TP
.BI @ flag
Pass
.BI -- flag
through to
.BR "codex exec" .
.TP
.B --
Stop wrapper option parsing.  Remaining arguments become part of the prompt.
.SH SANDBOX
Inside a Git worktree,
.B lord
always passes
.B "-s workspace-write"
to Codex, except in chat mode.  It never leaves a Git checkout in read-only
mode for repository-oriented work.
.PP
Outside a Git worktree,
.B lord
passes
.B --skip-git-repo-check .
Unix mode also gets
.BR "-s workspace-write" .
.PP
Chat mode passes
.BR --skip-git-repo-check ,
.BR --ephemeral ,
and
.BR "-s read-only" ,
and runs Codex from a temporary empty directory.  It does not install or wait
on a shared
.I AGENTS.md
profile link.
.SH FILES
.TP
.I $EXEC/etc/lord/AGENTS-repo.md
The repository profile.
.TP
.I $EXEC/etc/lord/AGENTS-unix.md
The Unix-filter profile.
.TP
.I $EXEC/etc/lord/AGENTS-book.md
The book profile.
.TP
.I $EXEC/etc/lord/AGENTS-chat.md
The chat profile.
.TP
.I ./AGENTS.md
Local instructions.  Real local files are preserved; internal profile links may
be replaced for the current run.
.TP
.I $HOME/.cache/lord
Timestamped captured outputs.
.SH ENVIRONMENT
.TP
.B EXEC
Root of the exec checkout.  If unset,
.B lord
derives it from the location of the script.
.TP
.B LORD_PROFILE
Default profile name.  Command-line profile selectors override it.
.SH EXAMPLES
.EX
echo INPUT | lord @unix "uppercase it"
lord @repo "fix the failing test"
lord @book "explain the semantic layer before editing"
lord @chat "what is a coroutine?"
lord @echo @repo "show me the codex command"
pray unix
.EE
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR codex (1),
.BR git (1)
